post_text:
Each Friday during remote learning, our students and staff make time to focus on social-emotional learning skills to support our students and staff as we all cope with learning from home. Last week, our district-wide theme was "Being Kind". MIS students learned kindness is universal across languages, beliefs and cultures. We also learned how an act of kindness can be the light in someone's dark day.

MIS students submitted ideas for our very first MIS Kindness Calendar. During the month of May, we invite all Medinah families to join in the fun by performing acts of kindness, to help bring light to our community!

MIS Kindness Calendar:
https://drive.google.com/open?id=1BIM8TE41IQCsk3OSHLbTzElSZluTYf5v

A reminder from Medinah Primary School:
Be an attendance hero and make the most of every moment you‚Äôre in school!

It is so important to be at school on time, every day. Supervision for kindergarten, first, and second grade students starts at 8:20 a.m. Drop your children off early so they can play with their friends before going into school. The tardy bells rings at 8:45 a.m. and that is when learning begins!
As a reminder, afternoon kindergarten starts promptly at 12:40 p.m. Morning preschool classes start at 8:15 a.m. and afternoon preschool begins at 12:45 p.m.

post_text:
WATCH D.O.G.S. is one of the nation‚Äôs largest and most respected school-based, family, and community engagement, organizations in the country. Since the program‚Äôs creation in 1998, more than 6,450 schools across the country have launched a WATCH D.O.G.S. program of their own. Each school year hundreds of thousands of fathers and father-figures make a positive impact on millions of children by volunteering millions of hours in their local schools through this amazing one-of-a-kind program. Who are WatchDOGS? Fathers, grandfathers, step-fathers, uncles, and other father figures who volunteer to serve at least one day a year in a variety of school activities as assigned by the school principal or other administrator.

http://dadsofgreatstudents.com/media/wysiwyg/support/ALL_ABOUT_WD_Color_2017_Sept_RVSD.pdf

The cost of the performance from ScienceTellers was mainly funded by the credit union and families really enjoyed the show.
